        <div class="program-content__section">
          <h2 class="program-content__heading font-display">What It Is</h2>
          <p>Eight weeks. At the end, you're placed on a civic board, advisory council, commission, or community decision-making body. Not someday. Now.</p>
          <p>You learn how local government actually works&mdash;budgets, agendas, Robert&rsquo;s Rules, public testimony&mdash;then get matched with a real placement in DFW.</p>
          <p>The goal isn't training. The goal is a seat.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="program-content__section">
          <h2 class="program-content__heading font-display">Eight Weeks. One Seat.</h2>
          <p>Each week targets a specific skill: civic mapping, public speaking, policy analysis, board dynamics, stakeholder relationships, application strategy, interview prep, and placement.</p>
          <p>Led by current and former board members, council appointees, and civic leaders who got their start young.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

